race.comment: EXCLUSIVE ARTIST (6) has been backed at each run this prep but a win has eluded her. Settled worse than midfield and raced wide before closing hard to be beaten just half a length over 1600m at Warwick Farm last start. Cherry ripe and crying out for this trip. Ready to break through. STING IN THE TAIL (8) is another finding it hard to score. Backs up seven days after a moderate performance over this distance at Rosehill. Gets in on the limit now and will run the trip right out. The consistent LUSKAIRE (4) kept the ball rolling with an effort less win over 1900m at Canterbury at his last outing four weeks back. All form this prep has been on rain-affected tracks which is the only slight query. WOUNDER (7) produced a real eye-catcher at Rosehill seven days ago and is right in this. KING PEDRO (1) has been gelded and resumes. Well found in early markets so must be respected.
